    <%# Comparison article %>
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>Key Differences Between BMI and Body Fat Percentage</h2>
      <p>
        BMI and body fat percentage are the two most commonly used metrics for assessing body composition, yet they measure fundamentally different things. BMI is a simple ratio of weight to height, while body fat percentage estimates the actual proportion of your body weight that consists of fat tissue. Understanding the strengths and weaknesses of each metric helps you make more informed decisions about your health and fitness goals.
      </p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
        <table class="min-w-full text-sm">
